---
// dog-training-classes.astro
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const registrationLink =
  "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdsBjQdPSqAgzqrLwaPaKG2dyvewv_a1sDMxIK1Vvp8/edit?usp=sharing";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <article>
    <h2>Comprehensive Therapy Dog Certification</h2>
    <p>
      Animal Assisted Therapy Services (AATS) MA provides a professional,
      multi-phase Therapy Dog Team Program designed to prepare handlers and
      their dogs for real-world volunteer or professional visits. After
      completing prerequisites like the AKC Canine Good Citizen certification,
      teams begin with a comprehensive four-hour handler lecture covering canine
      behavior, facility types, and safety considerations. This is followed by
      Phase I, a structured six-week class focused on mastering obedience
      commands amidst intense community distractions, and Phase II, which
      consists of four real-world shadowing visits alongside an experienced
      mentor team. The entire program culminates in a rigorous final examination
      testing the dog's response to medical equipment, restrictive handling, and
      unpredictable environments, ensuring graduate teams are uniquely polished,
      confident, and safe.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
